== Veggies and Balsamic Glaze ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced into ½-inch pieces).
Cut @broccoli florets{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim, peel, and
cut @carrots{9%oz}(trimmed, peeled, and cut on a diagonal into ¼-inch-thick
pieces). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Toss onion, broccoli, and carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large
drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp}. (For 4 servings, spread veggies out across entire
sheet.) Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender,
~{20-22%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet after 12 minutes).

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with half the
@dried oregano{1%tsp} (all for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add chicken and cook,
turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{3-5%minutes} (chicken will cook
through in the oven).

> Swap in pork tenderloin for chicken. Cook until browned and cooked through,
> 3-5 minutes per side, then finish cooking in the oven.

Once veggies have roasted ~{12%minutes}, remove #sheet{} from oven; carefully push
veggies to one side of sheet. Transfer chicken to empty side of sheet. Return to
top rack and roast until chicken is almost cooked through, ~{8%minutes} more.
(For 4, leave veggies roasting; transfer pork to a second #baking sheet{} and
roast on middle rack.)

While everything roasts, in a small #bowl{}, combine @balsamic glaze{5%tsp},
@Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, lemon zest, and @sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings).
Set aside.

== Herby Yogurt Sauce ==

Mince @parsley{1/4%oz}(minced). Trim and mince @scallions{2}(trimmed and minced).

In a second small bowl, combine @yogurt{2%tbsp}, parsley, scallions,
@olive oil{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges
for 4), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

== Glaze and Finish ==

Once chicken has roasted 8 minutes, remove sheet from oven (for 4 servings, leave
veggies roasting if needed). Carefully spoon half the glaze over chicken. Return
sheet to oven until chicken is cooked through, glaze is tacky, and veggies are
tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Transfer veggies to a large #bowl{} and let cool for at least ~{2%minutes}. Add half
the yogurt sauce; toss to combine.

Return pan with chicken to stovetop over medium heat. Spoon half the glaze over
chicken; cook, undisturbed, until glaze is tacky, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer
chicken to a cutting board to rest.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken and veggie jumble between plates. Spoon remaining glaze over
chicken. Serve with remaining yogurt sauce on the side.